Using a 'temp' TreeNode to store 'root'.

```
class Solution {
    public boolean checkTree(TreeNode root) {
        TreeNode temp = root; //Creating temp TreeNode
        int sum=0;
        root = root.left; //Traversing to left node
        sum = sum + root.val; //Adding left node value
        root = temp; //Returning to Root Node
        root = root.right;  //Traversing to right node
        sum = sum + root.val; //Adding right node value
        if(sum == temp.val) return true; //Final condition
        return false;
    }
}
```

