**Approach 1:** Using Multiset

Multisets are a type of associative containers similar to the set, with the exception that multiple elements can have the same values.
* Compare multisets of adjacent words
* If multisets are equal, erase next word and decrease the index
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<string> removeAnagrams(vector<string>& words) {
        for(int i=0; i < words.size()-1; i++)
            if(multiset<char>(words[i].begin(), words[i].end()) == multiset<char>(words[i+1].begin(), words[i+1].end()))
                words.erase(words.begin() + 1 + i--);
        return words;
    }
};
```
**Approach 2:** Using Map
* Make maps for adjacent words to count frequency for all letters
* If maps are equal, erase next word and decrease the index
```
