1.we don't need to count the times of each number because it is equivalence between [2] and [2,2,2] **->** use boolean array to reduce memory use.
2.we don't need to traverse each number after counting sort **->** when a single number x  apper in nums, x ~ x+k is the best way to partition (greedy).
3.we don't need to traverse from 0 to 10000 for every test case **->** recording the min/max value of nums and iterating over them.
4.if (k >= max-min) and (the size of nums > 0) **->** the answer is 1.

