solutions.content:
- The idea is to sort the array.
- If the array is sorted, we know that the smallest element would be at left end and largest at the right end of the sorted array.
 - Thus, to get the difference between minimum and maximum element, we can just find the difference between the first and last element of the sorted array.

 The algorithm can be described as,
 - Find the sum of first and last element of sorted array,
	   1. If the difference is less than or equal to k, we no longer need to divide the subarray further.
	   2. If the difference is greater than k, we will have to divide the current array into subarrays. 
	   The trick is that, we have to divide the current array such that the difference between largest and smallest element is less than the current difference. We can do this by pickup up next smaller element.

```
class Solution {
    public int partitionArray(int[] nums, int k) {
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        int result = 1;
        int end = nums.length - 1;
        int lastPartition = 0;

        for(int left = 0;left<nums.length;left++){
            int difference = nums[end] - nums[left];
            if(difference <=  k)
                return result;
            if(nums[left] - nums[lastPartition] > k || lastPartition == left){
                result += 1;
                lastPartition = left;
            }    
        }
        return result;

    }
}
```

