### Steps
1. sort the array
2. for each element:
2.1.  update the min & max
2.2.  if max - min > k, counter++ and reset the min & max
3. counter++ for the last one sequence

### Complexity
time: `O(nlogn)`
space: `O(logn or n)` depends on the sorting algorithm

### Java
```java
public int partitionArray(int[] A, int k) {
    int n = A.length, res = 0, min = A[0], max = A[0];
    Arrays.sort(A);

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        min = Math.min(min, A[i]);
        max = Math.max(max, A[i]);

        if (max - min > k) {
            res++;
            min = max = A[i];
        }
    }
    return res + 1;
}
```

