we keep on increasing the next pointer, if 
1. it is less than n
2. nums[next] - nums[start] <= k

once it fails the condition, i.e the start element and the last element (next) difference crossed k, we break out and increment the count of ans.

***we dont consider the last element (next) as it didnt meet the condition, and now we set the start to last element (next) as we start a new subsequnce.***

```
class Solution {
public:
    int partitionArray(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int ans = 0;
        int n = nums.size();
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        int start = 0;
        int next = 0;
        while(start < n){
            while(next < n and nums[next] - nums[start] <= k){
                next++;
            }
            ans++;
            start = next;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

